Most U.K. Investors Use Voting Rights, Poll Says, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-25T00:45:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/most-u-k-investors-use-voting-rights-poll-says-ft-reports.html
Nearly eight in 10 U.K. institutional
investors use their voting rights in all the companies in which
they own shares, the Financial Times reported, citing a survey
by the Investment Management Association.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
